== Attention ==
== Attention ==
==I'm >>d9324a8b-7ff1-42b4-8c13-9cb29c299bfe, everything up to this point wasn't enough to stop Zeronet from overwriting the code with the official one==.
Not even the "this is my own board" switch.
What I had to do was enable the read only property on the board files. I think setting it on index.html and index.template.html is enough but for additional safety create a zero-length all.js in the js folder, and set the read only property on everything but the 1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D\data folder.
==Also I've had to copy over the official contents.json== in the 1DdPHedr5Tz55EtQWxqvsbEXPdc4uCVi9D
folder, otherwise the board wouldn't load, lots of errors. **Admittedly it probably was my fault for deleting it in the first place**
==The way I finally got it to work was by deleting everything but the css, static and data folders and then running git and npm, copying over the contents.json, setting read-only on almost everything and only then running Zeronet==,
Godspeed anons.

>>1d587dc5-ed10-45bd-a8a3-39ad634da4c4
Tor poster here.
>and your seeding ratio will be like 100:1
Wrong. There are anons with weird ratios but it's not because of Tor, since I use it and I've been on a decent balance 100% of the time.
>what you call honeypots are actually seedbox for this page
If you have Tor on Enable on the seed box and the client has it too (and it's a default config) then the clients will connect through hidden services.
Just face it, no matter how much the Tor devs kvetch and whine, Tor is perfectly good for torrents. They just need to make the clients become relay nodes by default and if somebody's got a metered connection or something they can turn it off. And since this is .onion to .onion there's no concern about exit nodes being overloaded, since we never go through an exit node in the first place.

==Note: if you're using Tor and your tracker count reaches zero even with the extra trackers, and you have dynamic IP, just restart your router. I'm not sure why this happens or why this helps, but it works.==
